IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. INSERT-RECORD.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.

DATA DIVISION.
WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-STATUS-FLAGS.
    05 WS-DB-STATUS     PIC X(2).
       88 WS-SUCCESS    VALUE "00".
    05 WS-SQLCODE       PIC S9(9) COMP.
    05 WS-ERROR-MSG     PIC X(50).

LINKAGE SECTION.
01  LS-PARAMETERS.
    05 LS-PERSON-RECORD.
       10 PERSON-ID     PIC 9(6).
       10 PERSON-NAME   PIC X(50).
       10 PERSON-AGE    PIC 9(3).
    05 LS-RESULT        PIC X.
       88 SUCCESS       VALUE 'T'.
       88 FAILED        VALUE 'F'.

PROCEDURE DIVISION USING LS-PARAMETERS.
    PERFORM INSERT-AND-VALIDATE
    GOBACK
    .

INSERT-AND-VALIDATE.
    EXEC SQL
        INSERT INTO persons (id, name, age)
        VALUES (:PERSON-ID, :PERSON-NAME, :PERSON-AGE)
    END-EXEC

    IF SQLCODE = 0
        EXEC SQL COMMIT END-EXEC
        SET SUCCESS TO TRUE
    ELSE
        EXEC SQL ROLLBACK END-EXEC
        SET FAILED TO TRUE
        STRING "DB Error: " SQLCODE
            DELIMITED BY SIZE
            INTO WS-ERROR-MSG
        DISPLAY WS-ERROR-MSG
    END-IF
    .